{
  "text": "Dietary indices have advantages over data-driven dietary patterns. They are based on existing knowledge of optimal dietary intakes, provide summary measures of overall dietary quality, and are easy for the public to understand and interpret [CITATION_1] . Indices that test diets for several characteristics simultaneously are able to provide a measure of overall diet quality, which is impossible when only single nutrients or food groups are assessed [CITATION_2] .",
